  "prompt": "How is cancer caused?",
  "response": "Cancer is caused by several key factors:\n\n1. Genetic mutations\n- Damage to DNA in cells\n- Can be inherited or acquired during lifetime\n- Causes uncontrolled cell growth\n\n2. Risk factors\n- Age\n- Smoking\n- Excessive alcohol consumption\n- Obesity\n- Chronic inflammation\n- Exposure to radiation\n- Certain viruses (HPV, Hepatitis)\n- Environmental toxins\n\n3. Cellular changes\n- Disruption of normal cell division\n- Cells multiply uncontrollably\n- Ability to invade surrounding tissues\n- Formation of tumors\n\n4. Genetic predisposition\n- Inherited gene mutations\n- Family history of specific cancers\n- Higher susceptibility to developing cancer\n\n5. Epigenetic factors\n- Environmental influences\n- Lifestyle choices\n- Stress\n- Diet\n- Chemical exposures\n\n6. Immune system weakness\n- Reduced ability to detect and destroy abnormal cells\n- Compromised immune surveillance\n\n7. Hormonal influences\n- Hormonal imbalances\n- Certain hormone-related cancers\n\nCancer development is complex and typically involves multiple factors working together over time.",
